Reasoning: The paper deals with the performance analysis of a communication system in the presence of interference, which is a common problem in wireless communication networks. The use of selective relaying and the analysis of outage probability suggest that the paper belongs to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The consideration of multiple interferers and the use of closed-form expressions and asymptotic analysis suggest that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Communications (cs.COMM) sub-categories. Finally, the use of numerical simulations to validate the analysis suggests that the paper may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
